Few things in life are as enjoyable as settling down on the couch in front of your big-screen TV and unwinding with your favourite entertainment. Whether you prefer watching movies and TV shows, following your favourite sports events, playing video games in style, or simply require a high-quality display for the office – Takelot has got the TV set you need. Takealot stocks the widest range of TVs in South Africa – more than any traditional brick and mortar or online retailer. Many readers will recall Takealot’s Samsung TV Promotion during the 2019 Rugby World Cup. Takealot promised that any customers who bought certain qualifying Samsung TV sets would be refunded for their purchases should the Springboks win the World Cup. The company fulfilled this promise and refunded 346 customers a total of R4 million for their Samsung TV purchases. Campaigns like these show that Takealot is serious about its TV offering. Shoppers can choose from more than 200 TVs from 14 brands – including Samsung, Hisense, LG, JVC and Sinotech. With display sizes ranging from 28 to 86 inches, and all types of panel and design configurations available, you won’t have an issue finding the one that best suits your requirements. With pricing options range from entry-level to high-end TVs at R119,999, customers can find a TV that suits their budget. Takealot’s top-selling units include the Samsung 32-inch HD Ready Smart TV, and the 55-inch UHD TV, as well as the Hisense 50-inch UHD and 58-inch UHD Android TVs. Takealot currently has deals on the following TVs as part of its Fire Sale Promotion. <img class="size-large wp-image-340547 aligncenter" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Picture5-640x430.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Picture5-640x430.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Picture5-595x400.png 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Pictur